## Framework 1: Market Awareness (Schwartz)

**Source:** "Breakthrough Advertising"

| Level | Customer State | Your Strategy |
|-------|---------------|---------------|
| **1. Unaware** | Don't know problem | Story/identity first |
| **2. Problem Aware** | Know problem | Agitate, introduce solution |
| **3. Solution Aware** | Know solutions | Differentiate mechanism |
| **4. Product Aware** | Know your product | Objections, proof |
| **5. Most Aware** | Ready to buy | Best offer, simple CTA |

**Rule:** Messaging too advanced = no conversion.

---

## Framework 2: NESB (Milligan)

**Source:** "Take Their Money"

| Trigger | Question | If Weak... |
|---------|----------|------------|
| **N**ew | Fresh discovery? | Name unique mechanism |
| **E**asy | Achievable? | Add steps, time |
| **S**afe | Risk removed? | Guarantee, proof |
| **B**ig | Significant? | Specific numbers |

**Audit every headline:**
```
NEW:  □  EASY: □  SAFE: □  BIG: □
```

---

## Framework 3: Five Drivers (Warren)

**Source:** "One Sentence Persuasion Course"

> "People will do anything for those who encourage their dreams, justify their failures, allay their fears, confirm their suspicions, and help them throw rocks at their enemies."

| Driver | Copy Section | Template |
|--------|-------------|----------|
| **Encourage Dreams** | Hero, CTA | "Yes, you CAN [dream]..." |
| **Justify Failures** | Problem | "If you failed, it wasn't your fault..." |
| **Allay Fears** | Guarantee | "Worried about [fear]? Here's why..." |
| **Confirm Suspicions** | Agitation | "You suspected [X]. You were right..." |
| **Throw Rocks** | Enemy | "[They] don't want you to know..." |

---

## Framework 4: Cialdini's 7 Principles

**Source:** "Influence" (7th edition)

| Principle | Application |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Reciprocity** | Give value before asking |
| **Commitment** | Small yes → big yes |
| **Social Proof** | "Join 10,000+ [similar people]" |
| **Authority** | Credentials, logos, press |
| **Liking** | Story, shared identity |
| **Scarcity** | Limited time/quantity |
| **Unity** | "We" language, tribe identity |

---

## Framework 5: Loss Framing

**Source:** "Yes! 50 Scientifically Proven Ways"

Loss-framed messages are ~2x more effective:

| Gain (Weaker) | Loss (Stronger) |
|---------------|-----------------|
| Save 10 hrs | Stop losing 10 hrs |
| Get bonus | Don't miss bonus |
| More leads | Stop losing leads |

